# Lynx directory boundary (`lib/features/lynx/`)

## Product framing

- **Lynx** is Afenda‚Äôs **machine layer** for resolving truth, preparing work, and recommending controlled action ‚Äî an **ERP module** (`lib/features/lynx`), not a generic ‚ÄúAI‚Äù or chatbot product.
- **The Machine** is the **UI companion** (e.g. `ModulePageHeader` eyebrow) and the engineering name for the inference stack. **Vercel AI SDK** and providers are **implementation details only** ‚Äî not user-facing copy.

**Canonical line:**

```txt
Lynx is Afenda‚Äôs machine layer for resolving truth, preparing work, and recommending controlled action.
```

## Umbrella (modalities)

- **Lynx** is the **single product home** for machine-assisted cognition in ERP‚Äîwhatever **modality** you implement (retrieval-grounded answers, structured generation, codegen such as NL‚ÜíSQL **when explicitly bounded and governed**, chart inference, future layers). Those are **different shapes of the same machine layer**, not separate ‚ÄúAI apps,‚Äù chat products, or orphan routes.
- **Providers and mechanisms** (OpenAI vs Gateway, embeddings vs pure completion, Recharts vs prose) are **implementation choices**, not separate brands. User-facing surfaces still say **Lynx** / **The Machine** / layer names per below.
- **Engineering rule:** new modalities ship through **`#features/lynx`**, **`app/api/erp/lynx/*`** where HTTP applies, and **`lynx.contract.ts`** (extend **`LYNX_AUDIT_ACTIONS`** / layers when behavior becomes durable). Do not introduce parallel top-level ‚ÄúAI‚Äù or ‚Äúassistant‚Äù modules for concerns that belong here.

## Banned user-facing vocabulary

Do **not** use in product copy, nav, or `messages/*`: **AI assistant**, **chatbot**, **copilot**. Prefer **Lynx**, **The Machine**, and layer names.

## Knowledge vs Lynx

- **`#features/knowledge`** ‚Äî **substrate**: pgvector, `knowledge_chunk`, embeddings, chunk CRUD.
- **`#features/lynx`** ‚Äî **product**: Truth Retrieval UI, streaming truth, **Operator assist** (read-only tools + `streamText`), **NL‚ÜíSQL demo** (org-scoped `lynx_demo_unicorn`, guarded `SELECT`, Recharts), future Briefs / Canonical Intake / fuller Operator. Composes **`#features/knowledge`** via the **barrel only** (no deep imports).

Do **not** position ‚ÄúKnowledge‚Äù as the primary branded dashboard module once **`/dashboard/lynx`** is canonical.

## Lynx vs operational execution (Workflow DevKit)

- **Lynx** does **not** replace **Workflow DevKit** durable runs (`#features/execution`, `"use workflow"` / `"use step"`). Lynx stays inference/advisory; execution infra handles retries and multi-step operational pipelines (see **AGENTS.md** ‚Äî *Operational execution (Workflow DevKit)*).

## Canonical contract

- **`lib/features/lynx/lynx.contract.ts`** ‚Äî `LYNX_MODULE_ID`, `LYNX_LAYERS`, `LYNX_AUDIT_ACTIONS`. Derive audits, tests, and guards from here to avoid drift.

## Four layers (product names)

1. Truth Retrieval  
2. Operating Briefs  
3. **Canonical Intake** (code slug `structured` until refactored)  
4. Decision Operator  

## Phase 1 truth UX

Surface **retrieved evidence** (chunks) plus streamed **Answer**, **Limitations**, and **Next safe action** (see `schemas/truth-markdown.ts` parsing).

## NL‚ÜíSQL demo (structured query modality)

- **Purpose:** parity with [vercel-labs/natural-language-postgres](https://github.com/vercel-labs/natural-language-postgres) ‚Äî natural language ‚Üí SQL ‚Üí results ‚Üí auto chart suggestion ‚Äî **inside Lynx**, not a standalone app.
- **Data:** table **`lynx_demo_unicorn`** (`lib/db/schema.ts`); migration **`drizzle/0008_lynx_demo_unicorn.sql`**; seed **`pnpm lynx:seed-demo <organizationId>`**.
- **Safety:** server validates **single `SELECT`**, **no `JOIN`**, required **`"organizationId" = '<active org id>'`** predicate matching the session org, allowlisted **FROM** only; caps **`LIMIT`** (`nl-sql-demo-guard.shared.ts`).
- **Logic:** Server Actions in **`lib/features/lynx/actions/nl-sql-demo.actions.ts`** (`generateObject` from **Vercel AI SDK**); IAM audit **`erp.lynx.nl_demo.query`** (`lynx.contract.ts`).
- **UI:** **`NlSqlDemoClient`** on `LynxPage`; copy under **`Dashboard.Lynx.nlDemo`** in `messages/*`.

## Operator assist (tool modality)

- **Purpose:** Decision Operator preview ‚Äî models call **tenant-bound read-only tools** (session `organizationId` only); no mutations from tools.
- **HTTP:** **`POST /api/erp/lynx/operator`** ‚Äî Vercel AI SDK **`streamText`** + **`stopWhen`** step cap; IAM audit **`erp.lynx.operator.recommend`** (`lynx.contract.ts`).
- **UI:** **`OperatorAssistClient`** on `LynxPage`; copy under **`Dashboard.Lynx.operator`** in `messages/*`.

## HTTP

- **`app/api/erp/lynx/*`** only for Lynx streaming HTTP. Handlers thin; logic in **`#features/lynx`**.

## Imports (server vs client ‚Äî non-negotiable)

The main barrel **`lib/features/lynx/index.ts`** re-exports **Server Actions**, **`server-only`** data modules, and **async server UI** (`LynxPage`, streaming clients that sit under RSC composition). Importing **`#features/lynx`** from **`"use client"`** modules or from **Nexus shell chrome** (`components/nexus/**`) can drag **`next/headers`** / IAM audit / DB-adjacent graphs into the **browser bundle** and break the build.

| Consumer | Import door |
| --- | --- |
| `app/**` Server Components, Route Handlers, Server Actions, non-client lib | **`#features/lynx`** |
| **`"use client"`** anywhere (including **`components/nexus/**`**), Client Components under **`lib/features/lynx/components/`** that must stay client-pure | **`#features/lynx/client`** only |

**`#features/lynx/client`** ([`client.ts`](../../lib/features/lynx/client.ts)) ‚Äî intentional narrow surface: HTTP route constants (`LYNX_ERP_HTTP_ROUTES`), **`parseLynxTruthMarkdown`**, and **serializable types** needed for fetch/stream parsing (`LynxTruthEvidenceDTO`, `LynxOperatorNdjsonMeta`, etc.). Add symbols here **only** when they are **client-safe** (no `server-only`, no `next/headers`, no implicit pull of `index.ts` server graph).

**Forbidden:** `import { ‚Ä¶ } from "#features/lynx"` inside **`"use client"`** files unless you have verified the entire export subgraph is client-safe (default assumption: **unsafe** ‚Äî use **`client`**).

**Same-module exception:** Lynx **`components/*.tsx`** may use **relative** imports to **`../lynx.contract`** or **`../schemas/*`** for constants/parsers that are already client-safe; prefer **`#features/lynx/client`** when the same symbol is needed from **`components/nexus/**`** or other modules (respects **no deep `#features/*/schemas`** rule outside `lib/features`).

